### Customer phone-OTP auth (public mediator routes)
###
### These routes hide the pool's synthetic-email convention from the
### client. Mobile only ever sends/receives phone + OTP. See
### `backend/cognito-customer-auth/README.md` for the why and the
### deployed ARNs.
###
### Requires: {{baseUrl}} in http-client env. No accessToken needed.

### Start sign-in / sign-up (best-effort SignUp + InitiateAuth)
### → 200 { session, challengeName }; SMS lands on phone
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/customer/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "+15555550100",
  "name": "Test Customer"
}

### Verify OTP — returns access/id/refresh tokens
### → 200 { accessToken, idToken, refreshToken, expiresIn, tokenType }
### → 401 { message, session, challengeName } if OTP wrong (retry with returned session)
### → 401 { message } if session expired or too many attempts (restart from /start)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/customer/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "+15555550100",
  "otp": "123456",
  "session": "<paste-session-from-start>"
}

### Validation: bad phone format → 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/customer/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "not-a-phone"
}

### Validation: bad OTP shape → 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/customer/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneE164": "+15555550100",
  "otp": "abc",
  "session": "anything"
}
